# MetaMask Design System - Typography Tokens

This document defines the official typography tokens for the MetaMask design system. All components must use these values for consistent text styling.

## Usage

Always use design tokens for typography. Never use raw pixel values directly.

```tsx
import { typography } from "@/lib/tokens";

// ✅ Correct
style={{
  fontSize: typography.fontSize.base,
  fontWeight: typography.fontWeight.medium,
  lineHeight: `${typography.lineHeight.base}px`,
  fontFamily: typography.fontFamily.sans,
}}

// ❌ Incorrect
style={{
  fontSize: 16,
  fontWeight: 500,
  lineHeight: "24px",
  fontFamily: "Inter, sans-serif",
}}
```

## Font Families

| Token | Font | Usage |
|-------|------|-------|
| `fontFamily.sans` | "Inter", system-ui, sans-serif | All UI text |

## Font Sizes

| Token | Value | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| `fontSize.xs` | 12px | Tiny labels, badges, timestamps |
| `fontSize.sm` | 14px | Secondary text, descriptions, captions |
| `fontSize.base` | 16px | Body text, buttons, inputs |
| `fontSize.lg` | 18px | Section headers, large labels |
| `fontSize.xl` | 20px | Subheadings |
| `fontSize['2xl']` | 24px | Page titles |
| `fontSize['3xl']` | 32px | Large headings |
| `fontSize['4xl']` | 40px | Hero text, balances |
| `fontSize['5xl']` | 48px | Extra large display text |

## Font Weights

| Token | Value | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| `fontWeight.normal` | 400 | Body text, descriptions |
| `fontWeight.medium` | 500 | Emphasized text, labels, buttons |
| `fontWeight.semibold` | 600 | Headings, important UI elements |
| `fontWeight.bold` | 700 | Strong emphasis, CTAs |

## Line Heights

| Token | Value | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| `lineHeight.xs` | 16px | Tight text, badges |
| `lineHeight.sm` | 20px | Small text |
